pygraphviz
==========

About
-----

   pygraphviz is a wrapper to the graph data structure 
   of the graphviz graph layout and visualization package.
   See http://graphviz.org/ for details.

Requirements
-------------

   To use pygraphviz you need

      - Python version 2.3 or later http://www.python.org/
      - Graphviz http://graphviz.org/

Downloading
-----------

   You can download pygraphviz from http://sourceforge.net/projects/networkx


   You can browse the source at https://networkx.lanl.gov/wiki/browser/pygraphviz/trunk

   To access the repository using subversion, you will need a subversion client (e.g. svn for Linux). Then check out the code using

    svn co https://networkx.lanl.gov/svn/pygraphviz/trunk pygraphviz


Quick Install
-------------

   Tested on Linux.  In principle will work on any platform. 

   **Linux and OSX** (install from source)

      Download the source tarball, unpack, and run "python setup.py install". 

   **Windows** (binary installer)
 
      None available at this point.  Use the source package as above.

   Also may be installed using EasyInstall http://peak.telecommunity.com/DevCenter/EasyInstall

   easy_install pygraphviz	


Using 
-----

   Just write in Python

   >>> from pygraphviz import *
   >>> A=Agraph()
   >>> A.add_node("a")
   >>> A.add_edge("a","b","label")
   >>> for n in A.nodes():
   >>>     print n
   >>> for e in A.edges():
   >>>     print e.source(),e.target()


